LEXIUM — Complete Project Context Document
What is Lexium?
Lexium is a full-stack legal services marketplace that connects citizens (people seeking legal help) with legal service providers (advocates, mediators, arbitrators, etc.). It is a semester project for INT 221 at LPU, built to production-quality standards.

The platform has three distinct user roles — Citizen, Provider, and Admin — each with their own dashboard, workflows, and protected routes.

Tech Stack
Layer	Technology
Frontend	React 19, Vite, TailwindCSS v4, Framer Motion, react-router v7
Backend	Laravel 13 (PHP 8.4), MongoDB via laravel-mongodb ODM
Auth	Firebase Authentication (email/password) for Citizens & Providers; direct MongoDB bcrypt for Admins
Database	MongoDB (all collections)
Notifications	React Hot Toast (UI), SweetAlert2 (confirmations), Laravel Mail (email)
Deployment	Docker (configured for Render)
Frontend base URL (API): VITE_API_URL env var, defaults to http://localhost:8000/api

