Core Business Workflows
1. Petition Lifecycle (Full)

Citizen creates petition
        │
        ▼ status = 'pending'
        │ timeline = [{ action: 'submitted' }]
        │
Provider accepts OR declines
        │
  ┌─────┴──────┐
decline       accept
  │             │
  ▼             ▼ status = 'under-review'
'declined'    Auto-create Appointment (3 days out, 10:00 AM, status='confirmed')
              │
         Provider updates status via PUT /provider/petitions/{id}/status
              │
              ├── 'in-progress'
              ├── 'awaiting-documents'
              │
              └── When related Appointment is completed →
                  status auto-set to 'resolved'
                  │
                  ▼ (provider can close manually)
                'closed'
Status colors (frontend):

pending → yellow
under-review → blue
in-progress → indigo
awaiting-documents → orange
resolved → green
closed → grey
declined → red
2. Appointment Lifecycle

Citizen books → status='pending', reviewed=false
Provider accepts → status='confirmed'
Provider completes → status='completed'
                  → Transaction created (status='cleared', amount=provider.consultation_fee)
                  → Related petition auto-set to 'resolved'
Citizen reviews → POST /citizen/appointments/{id}/review
               → Provider.reviews[] appended
               → Provider rating recalculated (avg)
               → appointment.reviewed = true
3. Provider Reputation
Rating: Arithmetic mean of all submitted review ratings (recalculated on each new review)
Review Count / Rating Count: Incremented on review submit
Badges: Computed on each dashboard load:
"Top Rated Advocate" — rating ≥ 4.5
"Flawless Record" — 10+ completed cases
"Pro Bono Champion" — (shown in eminence, based on pro bono case count)
Tier (based on cases closed):
Tier I: 0 cases
Tier II: 5+ cases
Tier III: 15+ cases
Tier IV: 30+ cases
Tier V: 50+ cases
Standing: "Exemplary" if rating ≥ 4.5, else "Good"
Leaderboard: Top 20 approved providers ordered by rating DESC, then review_count DESC
4. Transactions / Ledger
Pending: Created when appointment moves to completed (initially in escrow)
Cleared: Finalized earnings available for withdrawal
Refunded: Disputed/reversed by admin
Admin can award bonus transactions directly (type = custom reason, status = 'cleared')
Provider can delete pending or refunded transactions (cannot delete cleared)
Ledger export to CSV is available
5. Admin Provider Approval

Provider registers → User.status='pending', Provider.status='pending'
Admin sees in dashboard → pending providers list
Admin opens provider stats modal → enriched details, earnings, badges
Admin approves → Provider.status='approved', User.status='active', is_verified=true
              → ProviderApproved email sent (if SMTP configured)
Admin rejects → Provider.status='rejected', rejection_reason stored
             → ProviderRejected email sent
