Known Patterns & Conventions
Backend resolvers: Every protected controller starts by calling resolveUser() or resolveProvider() to get the authenticated entity from firebase_uid.
MongoDB IDs: Always use $id->toString() or cast _id to string before returning JSON; the frontend normalizer handles {$oid: "..."} but string is preferred.
No hardcoded amounts: completeAppointment() uses provider->consultation_fee (not hardcoded ₹2500 anymore).
Petition → Appointment link: Accepting a petition auto-creates an appointment; completing an appointment auto-resolves the related petition. These are always in sync.
Reviews on appointments, not petitions: The reviewed flag and review submission is tied to Appointment, not Petition.
Timeline array: Every petition has a timeline array that logs every status change with {action, note, timestamp}. Initial entry is always {action: 'submitted'}.
Leaderboard route exists twice: Once inside firebase.auth middleware group and once publicly — both hit the same controller method.
